      • buildRepository

        public SesameAbstractRepo buildRepository()
                                   throws org.openrdf.repository.config.RepositoryConfigException
        This method has two roles: - Validating in depth the configuration : basic field validation + consistency of the OWL and mapping files (the latter is done when initializing the repository). - Building the repository (as an ordinary factory). This method is usually called two times: - At validation time (see validate() ). - At the repository construction time (see SesameRepositoryFactory.getRepository() ). However, the repository is only build once and then kept in cache.
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.repository.config.RepositoryConfigException
